== Lamb Koftas ==

If you're cooking your koftas in the oven not the BBQ, preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Put the @bamboo skewers{4} in a shallow dish of water to soak.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} in a large #bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and add the water (see ingredients for amount), mix together then add the @lamb mince{200%g}. Mix with your hands and shape into koftas around the skewers, 2 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Put on a #plate{}, cover and pop in your #fridge{} until ready to cook.

== Bulgur Tabbouleh ==

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the red onion, stir and cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @chicken stock powder{1}. Pour the @water{500%ml} for the bulgur wheat into a saucepan and bring to the boil. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Trim the @cucumber{1/2} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Pop the tomatoes and cucumber into a large #serving bowl{}. We'll add the bulgur and feta later.

== Honey Lemon Chicken ==

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Mix the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g} with the coriander in a small bowl and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Mix the lemon zest, half the lemon juice, half the @honey{30%g} and the @olive oil{15%ml} in a small bowl. Drizzle all over the tomato and cucumber.

Once the bulghur is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and add to the salad too. Mix together well, then crumble over the @feta cheese{100%g}.

== Cooking the Koftas ==

Place the koftas on a #baking tray{} and pop in the oven until browned and crisp, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turning halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle. You can do these on the BBQ, just make sure you turn frequently and check they are cooked through to the center.

== Honey Lemon Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @British chicken thighs{4} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the oil is hot, lay the chicken thighs in the pan and fry until golden ~{7-8%minutes} each side.

When the chicken is almost done, sprinkle on the @za'atar{1}, squeeze the remaining lemon juice into the pan and drizzle on the remaining honey. Allow it to bubble in the pan, turning the chicken thighs in the mixture to coat them evenly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Serving ==

Place the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} onto the BBQ or in the oven, and char/warm for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Serve the koftas and chicken with the herby yogurt dip, warmed tortilla and a serving of bulgur salad. Enjoy.